title: Country Music Made Me Do It
lyrics:
I'd sit in my bedroom strumming daddy's LG guitar,
Staring out the window at all those country stars.
Somehow that led me to a loaded down GMC,
Oil checked and all gassed up, headed for Tennessee.
No I never could have done it on my own,

Country music made me do it

Held my hand and walked me through it

Lead the way and kept me strong

It always does when I turn it on

There's always a high Lonesome song that keeps on pushing me along

I could take the credit but I always knew it

country music made me do it



I fell for a boy he talk to real good game

He was marbro Reds living on the edge and sweet when he said my name.

Well you live and learn yeah heartbreak hurts

And it was time for me to leave

Well it was hard to find my way out

I was in so deep. Yea but,



Country music made me do it

Held my hand and walked me through it

Lead the way and kept me strong

It always does when I turn it on

There's always a high lonesome song that keeps on pushing me along

I could take the credit but I always knew it

Country music made me do it



I couldn't have said goodbye

I never would've chased this dream

I've never left it and it's never left me



Country music made me do it

Held my hand and walked me through it

Lead the way and kept me strong

It always does when I turn it on

There's always a high lonesome song that keeps pushing me along

I could take the credit but I always knew it

Country music made me do it



Country music made do it



Made me do it
